ingredients:
118g unsalted butter

50g brown sugar
1tsp vanilla extract
1 large egg
150g all purpose flour
Â½tsp baking soda
chocolate chips

steps:
â mix together butter, vanilla extract, and both sugars for 5 minutes or until pale in color.
â add the egg and mix again until well combined.
â sift in the flour and baking soda and fold the mixture with a spatula. after combined, add in the chocolate chips.
â chill the dough for 15mins, then portion them using ice cream scoop and shape them using silicone mould. bake them in 175C for 20mins.
â after baked, air them out. in the mean time, pour in some melted white chocolate to the same mould. then, when the cookies are cooled enough, put them back into the mould. keep them in the fridge until the white chocolate coating is set.
